\begin{document}
\begin{equation*}Liver\;ER\;D4_{cort}=\;\left[\frac{\{(A_{D4cort}{\times}HAPF)+(PoV_{D4cort}{\times}PoV\;PF)\}-(HV_{D4cort}{\times}Liver\;PF)}{\{(A_{D4cort}{\times}HAPF)+(PoV_{D4cort}{\times}PoV\;PF)\}}\right]\end{equation*}\end{document} where ER is the extraction ratio, A is arterial, HV is hepatic venous, PoV is portal venous, HAPF (ml/min) is hepatic artery plasma flow, PoV PF (ml/min) is portal venous plasma flow, and Liver PF (ml/min) is liver plasma flow.

